data.chText: 优秀的；杰出的；出色的
杰出的运动员 / 成绩 / 成就
自然风景极美的地区
data.enText: an area of outstanding natural beauty

data.chText: 突出的；明显的；重要的
这一风景的突出特征
data.enText: the outstanding features of the landscape

data.chText: 未支付的；未完成的；未解决的
data.enText: not yet paid, done, solved, etc.

data.chText: 她未清偿的债务超过500英镑。
data.enText: She has outstanding debts of over £500.

data.chText: 许多工作尚未完成。
data.enText: A lot of work is still outstanding.

data.text: excellent ♦ outstanding ♦ perfect ♦ superb ♦ marvellous ♦ exceptional

data.chText: 以上各词均形容事物极好。
data.enText: All these words describe sth that is extremely good.

data.chText: 指优秀的、杰出的、极好的。
excellent尤用于服务或人们努力达到的标准：
data.enText: Excellent is used especially about standards of service or of sth that sb has worked to produce.

data.chText: 这些房间一晚上20元太合算了。
data.enText: The rooms are excellent value at $20 a night.

data.chText: 他英语说得棒极了。
excellent亦用以表示愉快或赞同：
data.enText: Excellent is also used to show that you are very pleased about sth or that you approve of sth.

data.chText: 你们都能来？太好了！
指优秀的、杰出的、出色的。
outstanding尤指做某事或在某方面杰出：
data.enText: Outstanding is used especially about how well sb does sth or how good sb is at sth.

data.chText: 杰出的成就
指极好的、很好的。
perfect尤指条件状况极好或很合适：
data.enText: Perfect is used especially about conditions or how suitable sth is for a purpose.

data.chText: 那是散步最理想的环境。
她想出了极好的借口。
data.enText: She came up with the perfect excuse.

data.chText: 指极佳、卓越、出色：
酒店的设施棒极了。
data.enText: The facilities at the hotel are superb.

data.chText: 指极好、非凡：
这食物闻起来香极了。
指杰出的、优秀的、卓越的。
exceptional多用以指人的能力或表现：
data.enText: Exceptional is often used about sb's ability or performance.

data.chText: 表现优异的学生免交学费。
data.enText: Exceptional students are given free tuition.

tr: having a quality that thrusts itself into attention
example: an outstanding fact of our time is that nations poisoned by anti semitism proved less fortunate in regard to their own freedom
a new theory is the most prominent feature of the book
a striking thing about Picadilly Circus is the statue of Eros in the center
a striking resemblance between parent and child
Einstein was one of the outstanding figures of the 20th centurey
did outstanding work in human relations

value.def: If you describe someone or something as outstanding, you think that they are very remarkable and impressive.

example.ex: Derartu is an outstanding athlete and deserved to win.
example.tran: 德拉尔图是位优秀的运动员，赢得比赛也是理所当然。
自然景色美不胜收的地方

example.ex: He was outstanding at tennis and golf.
example.tran: 他的网球和高尔夫球球技一流。

value.def: Money that is outstanding has not yet been paid and is still owed to someone.

example.ex: The total debt outstanding is $70 billion...
example.tran: 未偿债务总额达700亿美元。

example.ex: You have to pay your outstanding bill before joining the scheme.
example.tran: 在参加该项目之前必须结清余账。

value.def: Outstanding issues or problems have not yet been resolved.

example.ex: We still have some outstanding issues to resolve before we'll have a treaty that is ready to sign.
example.tran: 我们签协议之前还有一些未尽事宜待解决。

example.ex: The company is an outstanding example of a small business that grew into a big one...
example.tran: 该公司是小企业成长为大企业的突出例子。

example.ex: His mother, whose influence on his development was outstanding, came of a distinguished American family.
example.tran: 对他的成长影响深远的母亲出身于一个地位显赫的美国家庭。
